title: jmginer
author: jmginer
content: Hi, I bought WLUNA (Wrapped LUNA Classic) on Coinbase a few months ago.However this coin is no longer available.Where can I sell them? Thank you!

Thank you!I was wondering if you checked them on coinmarketcap?Â  If you bought them on coinbase then you want sell them and move them all back to coinbase so they can be sold there.I just checked your token, if it is correct this is the token you are referring to then you can sell it on DEX exchanges.https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/wrapped-luna-token/This is my first time seeing this token, how can you get it before. coinbase barely listed it on their exchange.

comments.author: tbct_mt2
comments.body: Quote from: jmginer on September 17, 2022, 10:08:12 AMHi, I bought WLUNA (Wrapped LUNA Classic) on Coinbase a few months ago.However this coin is no longer available.First it is bad when you bought WLUNA, not LUNC (Terra Classic). Why it is bad? Because what you bought is not real Terra Classic. Similarly, it is terrible if you don't buy BTC (Bitcoin) but buy Wrapped BTC.Second for your question, you can find answer by searching on Coinmarketcap.com.Below is link to available exchanges for WLUNA.https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/wrapped-luna-token/markets/

comments.author: MAAManda
comments.body: Quote from: jmginer on September 17, 2022, 10:08:12 AMWhere can I sell them? Based on data on Coinmarketcap, you can sell $WLUNA on several DEXs, including Uniswap, CronaSwap, CRODEX, Sushiswap and ShibaSwap. But after looking at the volume data of these various DEXs, I would suggest you sell them on Uniswap (V3), they have almost 100% $WLUNC trades there, which means you can easily sell your $WLUNC there.
